						<summary>

						<p>On a boulder in the tank called Vakrāṇi-Kere.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">16th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription in Kannada Script and Telugu language states that Siṅgaṇa, son of [Chē]gada Mallinēni, installed the image of Hanumanta and setup the lamp-post for the merit of his father. The present Mānvi was then called Mānuva <hi rend="italic">paṭaṇa.</hi></p>						

						<p>It is in characters of the 16th century A.D., and is dated in the cyclic year Vikrama, Karttika, Śu. 11, Thursday. It is difficult to ascertain the exact date in the absence of Śaka year.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
